Energy
        </emphasis>
stands as one of the most essential of all the earth’s resources. Human
life would not exist without the heat, light and food that depend on it. The
world consumption of energy has quadrupled in the past five decades. There has
been a very great increase in the use of non-renewable energy sources, notably
fossil fuels, yet most energy is inefficiently used.
